def: A Veronica. See Veronica, 1. [Obs.] Piers Plowman.A vernicle had he sowed upon his cap. Chaucer.

A European gold wasp (Chrysis ignita) which has the under sideof the abdomen bright red, and the other parts deep bluish green witha metallic luster. The larva is parasitic in the nests of other waspsand of bees.
A sea open to all nations. See Mare clausum.
A group of invertebrates including the Tunicata andEnteropneusta.-- Pha*ryn`gop*neus"tal, a.
The piece designed to protect the arm from the elbow to thewrist.
To satisfy the affinity of; to cause to become inert bychemical combination with all that it can hold; as, to saturatephosphorus with chlorine.
Directly; exactly; as, a due east course.
The south America alligator. See Alligator. [Sometimes writtencaiman.]
